{
  "text": "For a constant correlation \u03c1, the abstract optimization problem (3.1) has by Theorem 1 or from Tehranchi [CITATION_1] for t = 0 an explicit value, namely (3.3) with \u03b4 = 1 1\u2212\u03c1 2 . This expression is continuous in \u03c1 and increasing in |\u03c1|, for fixedP , and the intuition is as follows. The endowmentB is driven b\u0177 Y , whereas hedging can only be done in\u0174 which is imperfectly correlated with\u0176 . If the correlation between\u0174 and\u0176 is increased, better hedging is possible; so the value of the optimization problem (3.1) decreases. Note that (3.1) gives us minus the maximal expected utility.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "18543165"
